{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_018x8YPCzBqGaJ1AxJRKpSqd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pod is running but failing the readiness probe with a 503. CockroachDB's `/health?ready=1` returns 503 until the cluster is initialized. In insecure mode with a 3-node cluster, we need to run `cockroach init` after all nodes are started.\n\nBut the problem is that StatefulSet creates pods sequentially and waits for each pod to be Ready before creating the next. Since pod 0 needs all 3 nodes to join before it can become \"ready\" (in the sense of `health?ready=1`), we're stuck.\n\nThe fix is to use `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` in the StatefulSet so all 3 pods start simultaneously. \n\nOnce they're all running, I'll initialize the cluster with `cockroach init`, which will make the readiness probes pass. I could use `/health` instead of `/health?ready=1` to check liveness without waiting for cluster initialization, but that would skip proper readiness signaling. The parallel approach is cleaner—let all pods start together, then initialize the cluster.\n\nUpdating the StatefulSet...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":871,"cache_read_input_tokens":32107,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":871},"output_tokens":28,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"94e634c6-7de0-481f-bea8-c899d3d6850e","uuid":"5c69ba55-38a3-42cc-89d6-99ac5a225a82","request_id":"req_011CcfB3V2Z2ncWVJGJgEYVe"}
